nue to control our fate for centuries. Thoroughly readable, and, for all its honesty about the threats, as reassuring as it is frightening, A Planet of Viruses is a fascinating tour of a world we all need to better understand.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aViruses. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aDiamond, Judy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWood, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226320267423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226320267/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles